what is Husky?
Husky is a tool which is help to run the scripts automatically before or after git actions like commit or pushing code
before commit code husky will check is my code is formatted correctly using prettier  and run some tests and stop the commit if there is any problem 
Advantages
Husky saves the time by cathing the error early mistakes
Helps to keep maintain the code clean working code
Reducing the human errors while push and commit the code
Block the commits if the code is does'nt pass the certain tasks
Disadvantages
It takes to much time for commit and pushing
If the checks are written too strongly or too weakly then it block the developers for unnecessarily
Husky run locally only if the developr disables it rules might not be enforce


